            <p>Nintendo has released a new trailer for <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/metroid-prime-4">Metroid Prime 4: Beyond</a>, which shows off more gameplay for the game on the <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/digitalfoundry-2025-nintendo-switch-2-the-digital-foundry-hardware-review">Nintendo Switch 2</a>.</p>
<p>The trailer, which can be watched below, showcases both in-game cinematics as well as gameplay segments. Combat, scanning, and navigation are displayed on the latest Nintendo console, as well as a small glimpse of the motorbike segments too.</p>
<p>The trailer ends with a display of the three Metroid Prime 4: Beyond Amiibos coming out later this year, with both the Samus and Samus &amp; Vi-o-la (bike) Amiibos releasing on the 6th November. On the 4th December, fans can then grab an Amiibo for antagonist Sylux too.</p>

